It's your local kill file, right?

01:03:36.660 --> 01:03:38.780
Which is people I just don't effing want to hear from

01:03:38.980 --> 01:03:39.740
because they're obviously idiots.

01:03:41.440 --> 01:03:44.700
And your readers, news readers would respect that, right?

01:03:45.060 --> 01:03:57.860
And so something that Paul and I talked about years ago was a social K-file would be a way to have a social group be able to really just disincentivize and lock out the bad faith interactions.

01:03:58.740 --> 01:04:02.820
Now, of course, you could go too far with that and just create a little echo chamber for yourself.

01:04:03.600 --> 01:04:11.980
But there is a lot of space between spammers, trolls everywhere, spamming us with crypto spam and just total echo chamber.

01:04:12.320 --> 01:04:13.440
There's space in the middle.

01:04:13.780 --> 01:04:30.580
So I think what Bluesky is demonstrating with the shared block lists and things like that, and people just being able to mute things built into UI, those are the kinds of tools we can make available when the company and the technology isn't incentivized to create more angry bullshit sort of interactions and engagement.

01:04:31.540 --> 01:04:35.380
The algorithms don't promote that and push the heck out of it to get engagement.

01:04:35.560 --> 01:04:39.080
The default Bluesky algorithm is just chronological feed of following.

01:04:39.700 --> 01:04:42.140
So if you don't want to see somebody's stuff, don't follow them.

01:04:43.220 --> 01:04:47.120
You know, if you go to some of the other feeds, there's more algorithmic stuff there if you want to have it.

01:04:47.580 --> 01:04:49.580
But by default, it's just whoever you chose to follow.

01:04:49.750 --> 01:04:54.060
And if you don't like what they say and you know them, you should engage with them and say, hey, man, I don't agree with that.

01:04:54.360 --> 01:04:55.120
Like, let's talk about that.

01:04:55.760 --> 01:04:55.860
Right.

01:04:56.280 --> 01:04:58.720
So I think or unfollow them or just to follow them.

01:04:58.960 --> 01:05:01.480
It's like, you know, they talk too much about politician X, Y, Z.

01:05:01.620 --> 01:05:02.400
I don't want to hear about that.

01:05:02.540 --> 01:05:02.640
Right.

01:05:03.340 --> 01:05:04.620
It's it's a very simple approach.

01:05:05.300 --> 01:05:06.860
I need a space where I don't want to hear about that.

